This practice is focused on
supporting the organization

7
00:00:13,250 --> 00:00:15,890
strategies and plans
for service management.

8
00:00:15,890 --> 00:00:18,180
It does this by ensuring
that the organization's

9
00:00:18,180 --> 00:00:20,310
financial resources and their investments

10
00:00:20,310 --> 00:00:22,180
are being used effectively.

11
00:00:22,180 --> 00:00:24,470
So if you've ever decided
to make the recommendation

12
00:00:24,470 --> 00:00:27,490
to your boss that we should
go and buy X, Y, Z system

13
00:00:27,490 --> 00:00:30,600
or X, Y, Z software product
and install it in our system,

14
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,177
at some point, he's probably asked you,

15
00:00:32,177 --> 00:00:35,290
"Well, how much is it going
to cost and is it worth it?"

16
00:00:35,290 --> 00:00:38,440
Service Financial Management
is that whole backend process

17
00:00:38,440 --> 00:00:40,140
to verify that we have enough money

18
00:00:40,140 --> 00:00:41,950
to buy the things that you want to get

19
00:00:41,950 --> 00:00:44,040
and that what you want to
get is going to give us a

20
